House Resolution 555
By: Representative Burns of the 159th
A RESOLUTION
1 Congratulating and commending Craig and Diana Barrow, the inaugural recipients of the
2 Vince and Barbara Dooley Friends of the UGA Libraries Award; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, the Vince and Barbara Dooley Friends of the UGA Libraries Award was
4 established to honor individuals who make a profound difference in the lives of students,
5 faculty, and the university community through their support of the University of Georgia
6 (UGA) Libraries, thereby carrying on the Dooley's legacy of service; and
7 WHEREAS, Craig and Diana Barrow, distinguished alumni of the UGA Class of 1965, were
8 selected as the inaugural recipients of this prestigious award in recognition of their
9 unwavering commitment to supporting the instruction, research, and service goals of the
10 UGA Libraries; and
11 WHEREAS, the Barrows are the owners of Wormsloe, a coastal Georgia site of immense
12 historical, ecological, and archaeological significance originally settled in the 1730s by Craig
13 Barrow's ancestor, Noble Jones, and they have worked to preserve and enhance its role as an
14 educational and research resource; and
